==Regulating temperature== Engineering fins are also used as [[Fin (extended surface)|heat transfer fin]]s to regulate temperature in [[heat sink]]s or [[Radiator (heating)|fin radiator]]s.<ref>Siegel R and Howell JR (2002) [https://books.google.com/books?id=O389yQ0-fecC&pg=PA1 ''Thermal Radiation Heat Transfer''] Chapter 9: Radiation combined with conduction and convection at boundaries, pp.335–370. Taylor & Francis. {{ISBN|9781560328391}}.</ref><ref>[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/207095/fin Fin: Function in aircraft engines] ''Encyclopædia Britannica''. Retrieved 22 November 2012.</ref>
