{{Redirect|UNaM|entities with the acronym "UNAM"|UNAM (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox University |name =National University of Misiones |native_name =Universidad Nacional de Misiones |latin_name = |image_name = Logo unam.JPG |motto = |established =1973 |type =[[Public University|Public]] |endowment = |staff = |faculty =1,557 |president = |provost = |principal = |rector =Javier Gortari |chancellor = |vice_chancellor = |dean = |head_label = |head = |students =20,472 |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |profess = |city =[[Posadas, Misiones|Posadas]] |state =[[Misiones Province|Misiones]] |country =[[Argentina]] |campus =Ruta Nac. 12, Km. 7½ |free_label = |free = |colors = |mascot = |nickname = |affiliations = |footnotes = |website =[http://www.unam.edu.ar/ unam.edu.ar/] |coor = |logo = }}[[Image:Unam.JPG|thumb|234px|The '''UNaM''''s campus in [[Posadas, Misiones|Posadas]], [[Misiones Province|Misiones]]]]
The '''National University of Misiones''' (in [[Spanish language|Spanish]]: '''''Universidad Nacional de Misiones''''', '''''UNaM''''') is a public [[university]] in [[Argentina]]; founded by the law 20.286 on April 16, 1973, as part of the [[Taquini plan]], a program of reorganization of the top education that would take the foundation of universities of [[Universidad Nacional de Jujuy|Jujuy]], [[Universidad Nacional de La Pampa|La Pampa]], [[Universidad Nacional de Lomas de Zamora|Lomas de Zamora]], [[Universidad Nacional de Entre Ríos|Entre Ríos]], [[Universidad Nacional de Luján|Luján]], [[Universidad Nacional de Catamarca|Catamarca]], [[Universidad Nacional de Salta|Salta]], [[Universidad Nacional de San Juan|San Juan]], [[Universidad Nacional de San Luis|San Luis]] y [[Universidad Nacional de Santiago del Estero|Santiago del Estero]], form to more than 11.000 pupils, between them numerous foreigners, given their border location with [[Paraguay]] and [[Brazil]]. It has a [[publishing house]] and a radio station, ''LRH301 FM Universidad Nacional de Misiones'', that streams in [[Ogg Vorbis]] format.
