A '''Slip Line Field''' or '''Slip line field theory''', is a technique often used to analyze the [[stress (mechanics)|stress]]es and forces involved in the major [[deformation (engineering)|deformation]] of [[metal]]s, using theories based around maximum [[shear stress|shear]] stress￼￼. Slip lines are in fact directions of maximum shear stress in the body undergoing plastic deformation. http://solidmechanics.org/text/Chapter6_1/Chapter6_1.htm).
